  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 min]</span> to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil half kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based<strong> oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and remove the skin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> capers</strong>, <strong>black olives</strong>, <strong>gnocchi </strong>and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish and give everything a good stir</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> basa</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> dried basil</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the dish with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped basa</strong> to the dish and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the gnocchi has been cooking for 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and give everything a stir</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to the dish</p><p>Cover with the lid and return the dish to the oven for 5 min further or until the spinach has wilted and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>Neapolitan basa gnocchi</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-neapolitan-basa-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, give everything a good stir and season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Drizzle with some<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
